title: Persistent Choice (ADR-196 C2)
story: friendly-zoo
description: Parrot flavor cycles through variants with a once-only aside, and the cycle position survives save → restore via the persistent textState store (S12–S14, AC-8 end-to-end, AC-13).
---

# To the aviary, where the scarlet macaw lives.
> south
[OK: contains "Main Path"]

> west
[OK: contains "Aviary"]

# Examine 1 — cycle variant 0 + the first-time aside.
> examine parrot
[OK: contains "whistles a jaunty tune"]
[OK: contains "rescues from the illegal pet trade"]

# Examine 2 — cycle variant 1; the once-only aside is now gone.
> examine parrot
[OK: contains "Pretty bird"]
[OK: not contains "rescues from the illegal pet trade"]

# Save with the cycle counter at 2.
$save parrot-mid

# Examine 3 — cycle variant 2 (advances the live counter to 3).
> examine parrot
[OK: contains "theatrical disdain"]

# Restore: the world (and its textState counter) goes back to 2.
$restore parrot-mid

# Examine again — resumes at variant 2 ("theatrical disdain"), proving the
# counter persisted in the save. A non-persisted counter would reset to 0 and
# show variant 0 ("whistles a jaunty tune") instead.
> examine parrot
[OK: contains "theatrical disdain"]
[OK: not contains "whistles a jaunty tune"]
